## The LLM Integration Proposal

### Option 1: OpenAI API (The Standard Route)
- **How it works**: We install the `openai` SDK. You put your `OPENAI_API_KEY` into a `.env.local` file. The backend sends the Reddit post to GPT-4o-mini to extract the JSON.
- **Pros**: Effortless integration. Incredibly high reasoning quality. No heavy processing on your local machine.
- **Cons**: Requires you to paste a paid API key.

### Option 2: Ollama (The 100% Local Route)
- **How it works**: You download the local [Ollama](https://ollama.com/) application on your Windows machine and pull a lightweight model (e.g., `llama3.1` or `qwen2.5`). Our Next.js backend natively `fetch`es your local `http://localhost:11434/api/generate` endpoint.
- **Pros**: 100% Free. Total privacy. Truly a "local computer" prototype.
- **Cons**: Requires you to install the Ollama tooling. Uses your local system's CPU/GPU for inference, which means generating the "NYT View" will take a few extra seconds.

